7 An Act relating to driver licenses; authorizing
addition of certain designation to driver license;
8 requiring proof of eligibility; requiring interagency
coordination; allowing addition of designation at
9 certain times; requiring consultation on designation
design; requiring certain removal of designation;
10 authorizing the promulgation of rules; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6-126 of Title 47, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. Any individual who holds a valid lifetime hunting and
18 fishing license issued by this state may request the inclusion of a
19 "Lifetime Hunting and Fishing", "Lifetime Hunting" or "Lifetime
20 Fishing" designation on their state driver license or state
21 identification card. Proof of eligibility shall include, but may
22 not be limited to, presentation of the original or digital
23 certificate of the lifetime license issued by the Department of
24 Wildlife Conservation. Service Oklahoma shall coordinate with the
Req. No. 10738 Page 1

1 Depa rtment to verify the validity of the applicant's lifetime
2 hunting and fishing license.
3 B. An applicant may request the designation at the time of
4 driver license or state identification card issuance, renewal, or
5 replacement for no additional fee or an applicant can request a
6 replacement license at any time to add the designation for a fee of
7 Twenty-five Dollars ($25.00) in accordance with Section 6-114 of
8 Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes. The designation shall appear as
9 a symbol, text, or icon as determined by Service Oklahoma in
10 consultation with the Department.
11 C. Service Oklahoma shall remove the designation if the
12 lifetime hunting and fishing license is revoked or invalidated by
13 the Department.
14 D. Service Oklahoma is authorized to promulgate any necessary
15 rules to implement this section, including coordination with the
16 Department or updates to driver license design systems.
17 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
